@enrich: Replace each {DESCRIBE} below. Read src/parser.js for context.
  Rules: max 80ch, pipe|separated, abbrev (fn/ret/cfg/init/auth/db/msg).
  Save this file after filling all markers. Remove @enrich lines when done.
export parseFile()→parse,console.warn,imports.push,exportedNames.add,methods.push,extractCallsAndSQL|parse single JS file to AST|extracts classes,functions,imports,exports
extractCallsAndSQL()→calls.includes,calls.push,getCallMethodName,DB_METHODS.has,extractStringValue,isSQLString|walk AST to extract method calls and SQL queries
getTagName()|extract tag name from tagged template expr|handles sql,Prisma.sql,db.sql
getCallMethodName()|extract method name from CallExpression callee
extractStringValue()→templateToString|extract string from Literal or TemplateLiteral|replaces $N placeholders
templateToString()|convert TemplateLiteral AST node to string with $N
export discoverSubProjects()→resolve,join,existsSync,readdirSync,statSync,readFileSync|{DESCRIBE}
export parseProject()→resolve,findJSFiles,readFileSync,relative,parseFileByExtension,files.push|parse all JS files in dir|returns aggregated ParseResult
parseFileByExtension()→filename.endsWith,parseSQL,parsePython,parseGo,parseTypeScript,parseFile|route file to correct parser based on extension
isSourceFile()→filename.endsWith,SOURCE_EXTENSIONS.some|check if file extension is supported|excludes .css.js,.tpl.js
PATTERNS: AST visitor via walk.simple|extension-based parser routing
EDGE_CASES: ignores parse errors (returns empty)|excludes specific presentation files
